title: FCC adopts revised NGSO spectrum-sharing rules
summary: The Federal Communications Commission adopted new rules April 20 governing how fixed-satellite service operators in non-geostationary orbit share spectrum amid an unprecedented flood of proposed constellations.

title: U.S. Space Command announces new cooperation agreements with allies
summary: U.S. Space Command and the Australian Defence Space Command on April 20 signed an enhanced space cooperation memorandum of understanding.

title: Space Force procurement command rebrands commercial space office
summary: The Space Systems Command, a Los Angeles-based organization responsible for developing and buying space technologies for the U.S. military, is rebranding the commercial services office it established a year ago.

title: BREAKING! SpaceX Starship Experiences Anomaly In Flight
summary: This morning, SpaceX's Starship took to the South Texas skies for the first time in its fully integrated form.

title: So what was that? Was Starship’s launch a failure or a success?
summary: SpaceX's development process is messier, but it's also much faster.
